    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-04T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-04T17:00:00-05:00" n="434"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">898.00/6–249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-04T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 4, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>672. Dept assumes knowledge and distribution Peiping tels 917 and 928 Jun 2 (rptd
                    Emb 600 and 608, OffEmb 138 and 143) being restricted to you and immediate top
                    ranking members ur staff and desires every precaution be taken ensure even
                    receipt message not be known except by such authorized personnel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
